==English==

===Noun===

'''heavenly body'''  (''plural:'' '''[[heavenly bodies]]''')

# a natural [[celestial]] object, visible in the sky: a star, planet, natural satellite, asteroid, comet, the Moon or the Sun. Objects flying or moving in the atmosphere are not usually considered as heavenly bodies.

